data.description:
Back on the market at no fault of the sellers.
Walk into the entry of this completely updated home that has not lost its Old-World Charm. Nestled among the trees on almost 4 acres, with a park like setting. Sporting a huge front porch is a place for morning or evening coffee. Inside you will find a large dining room with copper ceiling and fireplace that is separated from the beautiful kitchen by an eating bar. Kitchen has a copper farmhouse sink, pantry, double ovens and counter tops are Quartzite. Two living areas divided by a fireplace along with a half bath is also downstairs. Upstairs is the master bedroom with walk in closet and bath with a large tile shower, Quartzite counter tops and claw foot tub along with 2 other bedrooms, each one having its own bathroom with granite counter tops. An office area is off the master bedroom.  The basement which is 1019 of the 4314 sq feet has had a makeover also. There are 2 bedrooms and a bathroom along with a large living/rec area and eating bar with sink. Then outside is a 30x60 insulated 3-car detached garage/shop with its own bathroom and separate hot water tank. Also, a storm cellar.
